   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">okay so this deck is designed by the normal player. one who buys maybe two packs a week.  it isn&#39;t that i am sooo  poor I just have more important things to spend my money on!  Anyway i have mainly been experimenting with magi...and these three seem to work fairly good together in this order.<br>
<br>
The trick is to get the balaments out with any thing else, using the spells, relics, and the epiks to eliminate anything that can get in thier lava doggie way.  Because of its low usage of a set amount of cards things can get tricky to stay in the game.  However this versatility works well because themadness is confusing to even the most stalwart player.  core kids scratch in confusion (hahahahhaha)<br>
<br>
Everyone tells me to use barak first but i think he is better as a second magi.  vorga is all about offense so use her like it!  i use barak to wear out the orothe players, and hold off the core till i get their good cards in their discard. and then once again sendin the lava doggies! <br>
<br>
built for teh poor man to make the rich man recognize! </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
